OL,6,FFather Brian D'Arcy opened the
OL,7,Fcommemoration at the site on the
OL,8,FBuskhill Road, hailing the survivors
OL,9,Fas "proving that music and goodness
OL,10,Fsurvives".
OL,12,F"That's what we're celebrating today,
OL,13,Fthe survival of good, music and peace,
OL,14,Fand joy and bravery," he said, adding
OL,15,Fa prayer for peaceful rest to all who
OL,16,Fdied at the spot.
OL,18,FAll those gathered said the Lord's
OL,19,FPrayer together, before the hymn Abide
OL,20,FWith Me was played.
